Accept two integer values from the user and return their product. If the product is greater than 1000, then return their sum

Input Format

Line 1: 1st Number value Line 2: 2nd Number value

Constraints

1<=num1<=10^7 1<=num2,=10^7

Output Format

Line 1: Result of the operation

Sample Input 0

10
20
Sample Output 0

200
program:-
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    int num1,num2;
    scanf("%d %d",&num1,&num2);
    int product=num1*num2;
    if(product>1000){
        printf("%d\n",num1+num2);
    }
    else{
        printf("%d\n",product);
    }

    /* Enter your code here. Read input from STDIN. Print output to STDOUT */    
    return 0;
}
